'''''5-25-77''''' is a [[coming of age]] film written and directed by [[Patrick Read Johnson]] and produced by [[Fred Roos]] and [[Gary Kurtz]]. It stars [[John Francis Daley]] as a teenage filmmaker living in [[Wadsworth, Illinois|Wadsworth]], [[Illinois]], and his excitement for the premiere of ''[[Star Wars (film)|Star Wars]]'' on May 25, 1977.<ref>{{cite web | last = DeMara | first = Bruce | title = Star Wars-inspired 5-25-77 a long, long time in the making: Director Patrick Read Johnson brings his nearly finished love letter to his own idealistic filmmaking youth to TIFF's Next Wave Festival. | date = 15 February 2013 | url = https://www.thestar.com/entertainment/movies/2013/02/15/star_warsinspired_52577_a_long_long_time_in_the_making.html | publisher=''[[Toronto Star]]'' | accessdate = 2 May 2013 }}</ref> Johnson began funding the project in 2001 and filming took place from 2004-2006. Additional shots were filmed in 2015 and 2016, making the filming course span a total of thirteen years.

The film was first known as ''5-25-77''; the title was then changed to ''''''77'''''. In 2012, the title was reverted to ''5-25-77''.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://newssun.suntimes.com/photos/galleries/12774830-417/wadsworth-director-has-new-hope-for-star-wars-flick.html |title=Wadsworth director has new hope for ‘Star Wars’ flick - PhotoGallery - Lake County News-Sun |publisher=Newssun.suntimes.com |date= |accessdate=2013-05-13 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140303092547/http://newssun.suntimes.com/photos/galleries/12774830-417/wadsworth-director-has-new-hope-for-star-wars-flick.html |archive-date=2014-03-03 |dead-url=yes |df= }}</ref>

The film had its official premiere on May 22, 2017 at the [[Genesee Theatre]] in [[Waukegan, Illinois]]. A short theatrical run followed.<ref>{{cite web|title='5-25-77' earns its long-sought moment in the spotlight|author=Moran, Dan|url=http://www.chicagotribune.com/suburbs/lake-county-news-sun/opinion/ct-lns-moran-star-wars-primere-review-st-0524-20170523-story.html|date=May 23, 2017|work=[[Chicago Tribune]]}}</ref> As of 2018 the film has not been released to the public in any format.

