{{More citations needed|date=April 2011}} {{Infobox book| <!-- See [[Wikipedia:WikiProject Novels]] or [[Wikipedia:WikiProject Books]] --> | name = Before Green Gables | title_orig = | translator = | image = Before Green Gables.jpg | caption = Cover of Viking Canada 2008 Hardcover | author = [[Budge Wilson]] | illustrator = | cover_artist = | country = [[Canada]] | language = [[English language|English]] | series = | genre = [[Children's literature|Children's novel]] | publisher = | pub_date = 2008 | english_pub_date = | media_type = Print (Hardcover) | pages = 400 | isbn = 0-425-22576-3 | oclc= 312933557 | preceded_by = | followed_by = [[Anne of Green Gables]] }}
'''Before Green Gables''' is the title of a prequel to the [[Anne Shirley]] series.<ref name="pengiun">Penguin Books ltd., Press Release: December 14, 2007.</ref> The book was published in 2008 by Puffin, a division of [[Penguin Books]], as part of Puffin's celebration of [[Anne Shirley]]'s centennial anniversary, which will also see the Anne Shirley series re-released to commemorate the event.<ref name="pengiun"/> The first book in the [[Anne Shirley]] series was ''[[Anne of Green Gables]]'', which was published in 1908.
The author of the prequel is Canadian children's author [[Budge Wilson]].<ref name="pengiun"/> In the official press release, Budge Wilson wrote: "I will, of course, try to be true to the astonishing character that [[Lucy Maud Montgomery]] created… But I would not – in fact, could not – presume to tell my part of Anne's history in Montgomery's voice. I will do this in my own voice, hoping that she would approve of the project if she were alive today."<ref name="pengiun"/>
== Synopsis == This book describes Anne's difficult pre-Green-Gables childhood, including the deaths of her parents. (Bertha -Mother-)<ref name="pengiun"/>
==Publisher== Three editions are available from different publishers: * Canada: Viking Canada (AHC), {{ISBN|978-0-670-06721-3}} * US: Putnam Pub Group, {{ISBN|978-0-399-15468-3}} * UK: Penguin Books, {{ISBN|978-0-14-138412-2}}
==Translation== ''Before Green Gables'' was translated into '''Japanese''' as a title of ''Kon'nichiwa Anne'' (meaning "Hello, Anne") and sold by [[Shinchosha]]<ref>[http://www.shinchosha.co.jp/book/211339/ こんにちは アン] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080709135425/http://www.shinchosha.co.jp/book/211339/ |date=2008-07-09 }} {{ISBN|978-4-10-211339-4}} and {{ISBN|978-4-10-211340-0}}</ref> and '''Polish''' as ''Droga do Zielonego Wzgórza'' (meaning "Road/Way to Green Gables"), published by [[Wydawnictwo Literackie]].<ref>[http://www.wydawnictwoliterackie.pl/ksiazka.php?ID=1893 Droga do Zielonego Wzgórza] {{ISBN|978-83-08-04308-0}} and {{ISBN|978-83-08-04311-0}}</ref> The book was also translated in French as a title of ''Anne... : Avant la maison aux pignons verts'' (meaning "Anne : Before Green Gables..."), published by [http://www.edtrecarre.com/ Trécarré].<ref>https://www.amazon.fr/Anne-Avant-maison-pignons-verts/dp/2895684391/ref=lh_ni_t_</ref>
==Criticism== Benjamin Lefebvre, co-chairman of the L.M. Montgomery Research Group wrote an article about this book.<ref>[http://roomofbensown.net/publications/eternally-anne/ Eternally Anne]</ref>
==Adaptations== The series was adapted into an [[anime]], ''[[Kon'nichiwa Anne 〜 Before Green Gables]]'', the latest entry in [[Nippon Animation]]'s ''[[World Masterpiece Theater]]'' series. It aired in Japan from April 5, 2009 to December 27, 2009.
==External links== * [http://lmmonline.org L.M. Montgomery Online] This scholarly site includes a blog, an extensive bibliography of reference materials, and a complete filmography of all adaptations of Montgomery texts. See, in particular, the page devoted to [http://lmmonline.org/before-green-gables/ ''Before Green Gables''].
==See also== *''[[Anne of Green Gables: A New Beginning]]'', a prequel television film released in 2008.
