{{Infobox company | name = Boomers! Parks | logo = Boomers! Parks logo.png | type = | traded_as = | num_locations = 14 |area_served = United States | key_people = | industry = [[Family entertainment center|Family entertainment centers]] | products = | revenue = | operating_income = | net_income = | num_employees = | parent = [[Palace Entertainment]] | subsid = | footnotes = | foundation = | location = | homepage = {{url|http://www.boomersparks.com}} }} '''Boomers! Parks''' is a chain of [[family entertainment center]]s which feature indoor activities such as [[carousel]]s, kiddie [[Swing (seat)|swings]], [[restaurant]]s, [[musical theater|musical shows]], and [[video game arcade]]s, and outdoor activities such as [[miniature golf]], [[kiddie ride]]s, [[bumper boats]], [[batting cage]]s, [[go-kart]]s, kiddie [[roller coaster]]s, and [[laser tag]]. The Modesto, Irvine, and San Diego locations each have a ride called the Flamethrower.
The Boomers! Parks brand is a [[Doing business as|DBA]] name adopted in 2001 by the [[Palace Entertainment]] chain, which was founded in 1998 through the merger of Camelot Parks, Palace Park, Boomers!, Grand Prix Race-O-Rama, and Family Fun Center. The official slogan of Palace Entertainment owned Boomers! Parks is "Where Family Fun Rules!".
In September 2014, Apex Parks Group purchased 10 Boomers locations from Palace Entertainment.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.latimes.com/business/la-fi-palace-entertainment-sells-20140918-story.html|publisher=Los Angeles Times|title=Palace Entertainment sells 14 entertainment centers and water park|date=September 18, 2014|accessdate=August 10, 2017}}</ref> In 2015, Apex Parks Group rebranded one of the last Mountasia Family Fun Centers to a Boomers; thus making 11 total Boomers parks owned by Apex.
