* With ''You Only Live Twice'' and ''Licence to Kill'' being notable  see, James Bond is almost always seen at the HQ of [[Secret Intelligence Service|MI6]] (referred to as MI7 in ''Dr. No'') in [[central London|central]] [[London in film|London]]. This has been the actual headquarters of MI6: the [[SIS building|Vauxhall Cross]] building on the [[Thames]] from ''GoldenEye'' (1995) onwards. Prior to that it was a nondescript building near [[Whitehall]], sometimes (''Dr. No'', ''On Her Majesty's Secret Service'', ''The Living Daylights'') ostensibly the HQ of [[Universal Exports]], the Secret Service's front company.

